Use MAUI's conditional compilation or the `OnPlatform` pattern with partial classes. The cleanest approach is **platform-specific service registration** using compiler directives:

```csharp
// MauiProgram.cs
public static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()
{
    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();
    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();

#if ANDROID
    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Android.AndroidNotificationService>();
#elif IOS
    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.iOS.IosNotificationService>();
#elif WINDOWS
    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Windows.WindowsNotificationService>();
#endif

    return builder.Build();
}
```

Each implementation lives under `Platforms/<OS>/`:

```
Platforms/
  Android/AndroidNotificationService.cs
  iOS/IosNotificationService.cs
  Windows/WindowsNotificationService.cs
```

All implement the shared interface:

```csharp
public interface INotificationService
{
    void Show(string title, string message);
}
```

**Why this won't break:**
- The `#if` directives ensure only the target platform's code compiles, so there are no missing API references on other platforms.
- Each platform file is already scoped by the default `.csproj` `<ItemGroup>` conditions MAUI sets up (files under `Platforms/Android/` only compile for Android, etc.).

**Alternative** — if you prefer no `#if` directives in `MauiProgram.cs`, use partial classes with a shared registration method:

```csharp
// Shared: Services/NotificationRegistration.cs
public static partial class NotificationRegistration
{
    public static partial IServiceCollection AddNotifications(this IServiceCollection s);
}

// Platforms/Android/NotificationRegistration.cs
public static partial class NotificationRegistration
{
    public static partial IServiceCollection AddNotifications(this IServiceCollection s)
        => s.AddSingleton<INotificationService, AndroidNotificationService>();
}
```

Then in `MauiProgram.cs`: `builder.Services.AddNotifications();` — no conditionals needed.
